"cloud_agreement_body" = "CLOUD SERVICE & DATA PRIVACY AGREEMENT

1. Cloud Services Overview
Strophe utilizes various cloud-based Artificial Intelligence services to provide advanced speech recognition (ASR), forced alignment, and machine translation features.

2. Data Transmission and Processing Location
By using the cloud-based features within Strophe, you acknowledge and agree that your audio data, video files, subtitles, and related text will be securely transmitted over the internet to remote servers for computation. These servers, including those operated by third-party AI providers (such as Baidu, Tencent, Alibaba, Moonshot AI, etc.), are primarily located within Mainland China.

3. Legal Compliance and Data Retention
To strictly comply with the \"Cybersecurity Law of the People's Republic of China,\" the \"Data Security Law,\" the \"Personal Information Protection Law,\" and other applicable administrative regulations in Mainland China:

- Data Retention and Logging: In order to ensure network operation security and assist in legitimate audits by relevant national departments, we will retain network operation logs, security incident records, and cloud service request metadata for a minimum period of six (6) months, as mandated by Article 21 of the Cybersecurity Law.

- Data Security and Privacy: Your media data is used strictly for executing the transcription or translation tasks you request. We promise not to use your private media data to train our own core models without your authorization. However, please note that when data flows through third-party cloud service providers, it is also subject to the standard data retention and censorship policies established by those providers in compliance with Mainland Chinese laws.

4. Third-Party Custom LLM Disclaimer
Strophe allows you to manually add and configure third-party Large Language Model (LLM) APIs for machine translation. Please note that any custom third-party services you add yourself are NOT under our supervision or regulation. When using these services, you must consciously abide by your local laws and regulations, as well as the terms of service and legal regulations of the respective third-party provider.

5. User Consent & Opt-Out
By enabling and utilizing the cloud features, you explicitly consent to your data being transmitted to servers in Mainland China for computation, and you agree to the aforementioned log retention and data processing rules.

If you have any doubts or concerns regarding the processing of cloud content, you may choose not to use the cloud services we provide. You can always switch to Strophe's purely local (On-Device) offline processing mode, where all data is computed entirely on your device and is never uploaded.";
